OL,3,CMohamud Hassan: 'No evidence' that
OL,4,Cofficers' actions contributed to death
OL,6,FIt also identified "areas of learning"
OL,7,Ffor South Wales Police. These included
OL,8,Fthe safe management of potentially
OL,9,Fvulnerable detainees, as the level of
OL,10,Fservice Mr Hassan received in custody
OL,11,Fsometimes "fell below the standard
OL,12,Frequired".
OL,14,FThe IOPC identified the need for
OL,15,Fimproved maintenance of CCTV, as some
OL,16,Fof the equipment was broken and this
OL,17,Fcould have led to the loss of
OL,18,Fevidence. Other footage could not be
OL,19,Fsecured which "could have also caused
OL,20,Fwhat may have been significant
OL,21,Fevidence to be lost".
